We associate both sets of fields by a Fourier transform: \[
\begin{align}
F(\omega) & = \int\limits_{-\infty}^\infty f(t) e^{-i\omega t}\,\mathrm d t \\
f(t) & = \frac{1}{2\pi} \int\limits_{-\infty}^\infty F(\omega) e^{i\omega t}\,\mathrm d\omega
\end{align}
